a:2:{s:7:"content";s:1171:"<h2>Hybrid drawing techniques for interior design</h2>
<h3>By Jorge,Paricio</h3>
<p>The book comprises detailed and illustrated instructions on interior design using techniques like freehand drawing and digital artwork. Each chapter is arranged thematically focusing on aspects of design such as working with furniture, hard and soft surfaces, light and shadow, floor plans and elevation, and external landscape and architecture. Through specific examples of items, the book provides detailed instructions on applying design software like Photoshop and Sketchbook along with freehand sketching. </p>
<p><strong>Publication Date:</strong> 2019</p>
<p><strong>Expertise Level:</strong> Advanced</p>
<p><strong>Intended Audience:</strong> College/University</p>
